title: MAFS' Jules Robinson steps out solo as she leads the celebrity arrivals at the Blow Bar Co Launch
text:
She's reportedly going through a 'rough patch' with her fiancé Cameron Merchant after postponing their wedding date.

And on Tuesday, Married At First Sight's Jules Robinson stepped out solo as she lead the celebrity arrivals at the Blow Bar Co Waverley Launch in Sydney.

The 37-year-old reality star was a a vision as she turned heads in red plaid pants suit.

Where's Cameron? MAFS' Jules Robinson (pictured) stepped out solo as she lead the celebrity arrivals in a red plaid pants suit at the Blow Bar Co Launch in Waverley on Tuesday night

The Weight Watchers ambassador opted for a matching red top, worn under her jacket.

Jules accessorized her look with a designer handbag, which she clutched onto while she posed for photos.

She completed her look in cream coloured heels, which featured a curved design and mesh panel.

Red hot: The 37-year-old reality star was a a vision as she turned heads in red plaid pants suit

The Daily Edition host Sally Obermeder was also in attendance, opting for a monochrome look.

The 46-year-old Seven personality stunned in an all-black ensemble consisting of a jumpsuit.

She added strappy heels and wore her brunette hair down around her shoulders, beaming as she posed along the media wall.

Star power! The Daily Edition host Sally Obermeder was also in attendance, carrying a YSL bag

Sally completed her look with a Yves Saint Laurent handbag which she carried in one hand.

The brunette stunner showed off her natural complexion, opting for a neutral makeup palette.

She wore a light shade of foundation and eyeliner, along with a nude lipstick in a gloss finish.

Smiles: The 46-year-old Seven personality stunned in an all-black ensemble

The cocktail launch party hosted at the new Bronte location, also featured appearances by The Bachelor's Sogand Mohta and Emma Roche.

Sogan, who failed to match with Matt Agnew, put on a leggy display in a bright mini yellow dress.

She opted for peachy makeup and plum-toned eye-shadow, and carried a designer handbag.

Stunners! The cocktail launch party hosted at the new Bronte location, also featured appearances by The Bachelor's Sogand Mohta (left) and Emma Roche (right)

Meanwhile, fellow suitor Emma also showed off her toned pins in ruffled white dress with a belted waist.

She added a pair of blush-toned heels, and a makeup look consisting of pink lipstick and matching eye-shadow.

The Bachelor rejects looked to be in good spirits as they even posed for a snap together during the event.
description: She's reportedly going through a 'rough patch' with her fiancé Cameron Merchant after postponing their wedding date.
authors: Ali Daher For Daily Mail Australia
